dxf2svg.util   
 

Uses of Processor in dxf2svg.util
 

Subclasses of Processor in dxf2svg.util
 class BlockProcessor
          The BlockProcessor reads an Entity Pair List and breaks the Dxf blocks into SvgSymbols.
 class DxfObjectProcessor
          The ObjectProcessor reads an Entity Pairs looking for important informtion concerning images that may be embedded.
 class EntityProcessor
          The EntityProcessor maps the data from a DXF into equivelant SvgObjects.
 class HeaderProcessor
          This class reads the container (Vector) of variables from the DXF header and populates variables that will be useful for generating the SVG.
 class TableProcessor
          Like the other Processor objects, TableProcessor unpackages the Vector it receives from DxfConverter and searches it for table boundaries.
